Symbol.name: Sb_allowevent
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates if events are placed in the events queue as soon as they are detected

Symbol.name: Sb_asciicom1
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, this bit allows to configure ASCII protocol on Serial Line 1

Symbol.name: Sb_asciicom2
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, this bit allows to configure ASCII protocol on Serial Line 2

Symbol.name: Sb_autoeth
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, this bit allows to force some specific Ethernet configuration set in %S35 and %S36

Symbol.name: Sb_batstatus
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, external battery power is low, or no external battery is detected

Symbol.name: Sb_coldstart
Symbol.Comment: Indicates or executes a cold start (data initialized to default values)

Symbol.name: Sb_confeth
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1 (if there is no post configuration in use), this bit allows to set new Ethernet configuration by %SW33 to %SW38

Symbol.name: Sb_dalarm
Symbol.Comment: The display will switch automatically to the alarm page

Symbol.name: Sb_dateupdate
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, the date and time are incremented or decremented according to the rising edges on the control bits set in %SW59

Symbol.name: Sb_dred
Symbol.Comment: The Display backlight will be red as long as an alarm is active

Symbol.name: Sb_duplexmode
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates Ethernet Duplex mode. Set to 0 if Half Duplex, Set to 1 if Full Duplex

Symbol.name: Sb_firstrun
Symbol.Comment: Indicates the first controller cycle in RUN mode

Symbol.name: Sb_freezegrafcet
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, this bit validates the pre-positioning of GRAFCET. Maintaining this bit at 1 freezes the GRAFCET (freezes the chart)

Symbol.name: Sb_inderror
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates an index overflow of the indexed object address when a 16 bit operation is performed

Symbol.name: Sb_inforced
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates there is at least one input forced

Symbol.name: Sb_initgrafcet
Symbol.Comment: At state 1, this bit causes GRAFCET initialization. Active steps are deactivated and initial steps are activated

Symbol.name: Sb_iocombus
Symbol.Comment: I/O communication is running correctly (1), I/O communication error detected (0)

Symbol.name: Sb_ioerror
Symbol.Comment: This bit is set to 0 when an I/O communication interruption is detected on the base controller

Symbol.name: Sb_ioforced
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates there is at least one input or output forced

Symbol.name: Sb_lastbit
Symbol.Comment: It indicates the value of the last ejected bit

Symbol.name: Sb_lostevent
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates if there is a saturation of events queue

Symbol.name: Sb_mbaddress
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, the address can be changed by changing the values of %SW101 (port 1) or %SW102 (port 2)

Symbol.name: Sb_modinit
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, this bit allows to initialize the modem, see also %SW167

Symbol.name: Sb_mwbackup
Symbol.Comment: User set this bit to 1 to store the %MW variable in the flash (up to 1000)

Symbol.name: Sb_mwerase
Symbol.Comment: User sets this bit to 1 to erase all %MW variables in the flash memory

Symbol.name: Sb_mwrestore
Symbol.Comment: User set this bit to 1 to restore the saved data

Symbol.name: Sb_mwsaved
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1 if there is valid data saved on flash

Symbol.name: Sb_operror
Symbol.Comment: It indicates an overflow when a 16 bit operation is performed

Symbol.name: Sb_outforced
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates there is at least one output forced

Symbol.name: Sb_overrun
Symbol.Comment: It indicates scan time greater than the period defined by the user

Symbol.name: Sb_progbackup
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, the backup program is valid

Symbol.name: Sb_rearmoutputs
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, the automatic re-arming of outputs following a short circuit is enabled

Symbol.name: Sb_resetgrafcet
Symbol.Comment: At state 1, this bit causes the active steps of the entire GRAFCET to be deactivated

Symbol.name: Sb_rtcerror
Symbol.Comment: At state 1, the date and time must be initialized

Symbol.name: Sb_rtcstatus
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, the date and time must be initialized by the user

Symbol.name: Sb_rtcupdate
Symbol.Comment: Set to 1, this bit allows to update the date and time

Symbol.name: Sb_runmode
Symbol.Comment: The controller is running

Symbol.name: Sb_speedeth
Symbol.Comment: This bit indicates Ethernet speed. Set to 0 if 10 Mbps, Set to 1 if 100 Mbps

Symbol.name: Sb_tb100ms
Symbol.Comment: Time base of 100 ms generated by an internal clock

Symbol.name: Sb_tb10ms
Symbol.Comment: Time base of 10 ms generated by an internal clock

Symbol.name: Sb_tb1min
Symbol.Comment: Time base of 1 min generated by an internal clock

Symbol.name: Sb_tb1s
Symbol.Comment: Time base of 1 s generated by an internal clock

Symbol.name: Sb_warmstart
Symbol.Comment: Indicates there was a warm start with data backup

Symbol.name: Sb_watchdog
Symbol.Comment: Watchdog overflow causes the controller to change to HALT

Symbol.name: Sw_adjustdate
Symbol.Comment: Contains two sets of 8 bits to adjust current date.The operation is always performed on rising edge of the bit. This word is enabled by bit %S59

Symbol.name: Sw_anastatus
Symbol.Comment: Each bit indicate status of the embedded analog inputs

Symbol.name: Sw_bootversion
Symbol.Comment: Contains the boot version of the controller

Symbol.name: Sw_car1status
Symbol.Comment: Shows the status code for the Cartridge 1 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_car2status
Symbol.Comment: Shows the status code for the Cartridge 2 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_comversion
Symbol.Comment: Contains the commercial version of the controller

Symbol.name: Sw_contid
Symbol.Comment: Contains the logic controller code ID. For more information, refer to the M221 Logic Controller Code ID table

Symbol.name: Sw_controliobus
Symbol.Comment: Shows IO bus controller status (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_controlstatus
Symbol.Comment: Controller Status: NO CONFIG (0), STOP (2), RUN (3), HALT (4), POWERLESS MODE (5)

Symbol.name: Sw_countd1
Symbol.Comment: Down Counter 1, decremented individually by the system every ms

Symbol.name: Sw_countd2
Symbol.Comment: Down Counter 2, decremented individually by the system every ms

Symbol.name: Sw_countd3
Symbol.Comment: Down Counter 3, decremented individually by the system every ms

Symbol.name: Sw_countd4
Symbol.Comment: Down Counter 4, decremented individually by the system every ms

Symbol.name: Sw_cpuload
Symbol.Comment: Shows percentage of processing load

Symbol.name: Sw_dindex
Symbol.Comment: Contains the Display page INDEX and allows to choose an other page

Symbol.name: Sw_dsperror
Symbol.Comment: Remote Graphic Display last error detected

Symbol.name: Sw_dspstate
Symbol.Comment: Remote Graphic Display connection state

Symbol.name: Sw_dspversion
Symbol.Comment: Contains the version of the Remote Graphic Display

Symbol.name: Sw_ev0avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 0 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev0time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 0 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_ev1avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 1 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev1time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 1 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_ev2avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 2 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev2time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 2 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_ev3avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 3 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev3time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 3 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_ev4avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 4 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev4time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 4 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_ev5avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 5 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev5time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 5 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_ev6avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 6 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev6time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 6 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_ev7avgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of event 7 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_ev7time
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the event 7 in us (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_exch1error
Symbol.Comment: Contains EXCH1 error code, see online help for details

Symbol.name: Sw_exch2error
Symbol.Comment: Contains EXCH2 error code, see online help for details

Symbol.name: Sw_exe1micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.2 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe1ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.2 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_exe2micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.3 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe2ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.3 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_exe3micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.4 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe3ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.4 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_exe4micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.5 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe4ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event input %I0.5 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_exe5micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event Threshold 0 of HSC0 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe5ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event threshold 0 of HSC0 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_exe6micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event Threshold 1 of HSC0 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe6ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event threshold 1 of HSC0 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_exe7micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event Threshold 0 of HSC1 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe7ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event threshold 0 of HSC1 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_exe8micros
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event Threshold 1 of HSC1 in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_exe8ms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the event threshold 1 of HSC1 in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_floatstatus
Symbol.Comment: Default status when an error is detected in a floating arithmetic operation (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_fw1version
Symbol.Comment: Contains the Firmware version of the controller (1st word)

Symbol.name: Sw_fw2version
Symbol.Comment: Contains the Firmware version of the controller (2° word)

Symbol.name: Sw_iooption
Symbol.Comment: Shows optional expansion module configuration (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_iostatus
Symbol.Comment: Shows expansion I/O module status (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_lastscan1
Symbol.Comment: Shows execution time of the last controller scan cycle (in ms).If the scan time is 2,250 ms, %SW30 = 2 and %SW70 = 250

Symbol.name: Sw_lastscan2
Symbol.Comment: Shows the microseconds of the execution time of the last controller scan cycle. If the scan time is 2,250 ms the %SW30 will be 2 and the %SW70 = 250

Symbol.name: Sw_laststop
Symbol.Comment: Displays code giving cause of last stop: Run/Stop input edge,Stop at software detected fault, Stop command, Power outage,Stop at hardware detected fault

Symbol.name: Sw_ls1time
Symbol.Comment: Time of the last power failure or controller stop (in BCD): SS Seconds

Symbol.name: Sw_ls2time
Symbol.Comment: Time of the last power failure or controller stop (in BCD): HHMM Hour and minute

Symbol.name: Sw_ls3time
Symbol.Comment: Time of the last power failure or controller stop (in BCD): MMDD Month and day

Symbol.name: Sw_ls4time
Symbol.Comment: Time of the last power failure or controller stop (in BCD): CCYY Century and year

Symbol.name: Sw_mastertask
Symbol.Comment: Modifies controller scan period defined at configuration through the user program in the Animation Table Editor

Symbol.name: Sw_maxscan1
Symbol.Comment: Shows execution time of the longest controller scan cycle since last cold start (in ms). If the scan time is 2,250 ms, %SW31 = 2 and %SW71 = 250

Symbol.name: Sw_maxscan2
Symbol.Comment: Shows the microseconds of the execution time of the longest controller scan cycle since the last cold start. If the scan time is 2,250 ms the %SW31 will be 2 and the %SW71 = 250

Symbol.name: Sw_minscan1
Symbol.Comment: Shows execution time of shortest controller scan cycle since the last cold start (in ms). If the scan time is 2,250 ms, %SW32 = 2 and %SW72 = 250

Symbol.name: Sw_minscan2
Symbol.Comment: Shows the microseconds of the execution time of shortest controller scan cycle since the last cold start. If the scan time is 2,250 ms the %SW32 will be 2 and the %SW72 = 250

Symbol.name: Sw_modstatus
Symbol.Comment: Describes the answer of the modem to the last init command

Symbol.name: Sw_nbevents
Symbol.Comment: Shows how many events have been executed since the last cold start

Symbol.name: Sw_nbpers
Symbol.Comment: Number of persistent variables (maximum 1,000)

Symbol.name: Sw_nbsl1error
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames received in error by the Serial Line 1

Symbol.name: Sw_nbsl1frames
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames transmitted by the Serial Line 1

Symbol.name: Sw_nbsl1ok
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames correctly received by the Serial Line 1

Symbol.name: Sw_nbsl2error
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames received in error by the Serial Line 2

Symbol.name: Sw_nbsl2frames
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames transmitted by the Serial Line 2

Symbol.name: Sw_nbsl2ok
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames correctly received by the Serial Line 2

Symbol.name: Sw_nbusberror
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames received in error by the USB channel

Symbol.name: Sw_nbusbframes
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames transmitted by the USB channel

Symbol.name: Sw_nbusbok
Symbol.Comment: Counts the number of frames correctly received by the USB channel

Symbol.name: Sw_outprot
Symbol.Comment: Shows the protection error status of output blocks

Symbol.name: Sw_peravgms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time (last 5 times) of the PERIODIC task in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_perlast
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the periodic task in µs

Symbol.name: Sw_perlastms
Symbol.Comment: Shows the last execution time of the PERIODIC task in ms

Symbol.name: Sw_pertask
Symbol.Comment: Modifies the cycle time [2...255 ms] of the Periodic task

Symbol.name: Sw_pertime
Symbol.Comment: Shows the average execution time of the periodic task in µs (last 5 times)

Symbol.name: Sw_rtcccyy
Symbol.Comment: RTC Function: contains in BCD CCYY: century and year

Symbol.name: Sw_rtcday
Symbol.Comment: RTC Function: contains in BCD xN Day of the week (N=1 for Monday)

Symbol.name: Sw_rtchhmm
Symbol.Comment: RTC Function: contains in BCD HHMM: hour and minute

Symbol.name: Sw_rtcmmdd
Symbol.Comment: RTC Function: contains in BCD MMDD: month and day

Symbol.name: Sw_rtcsec
Symbol.Comment: RTC Function: contains in BCD 00SS Seconds

Symbol.name: Sw_saverestore
Symbol.Comment: Contains the command and/or diagnostics for save/restore function of application program (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_sch_enable
Symbol.Comment: Enables or disables operation of schedule blocks by the user program or operator display

Symbol.name: Sw_signature
Symbol.Comment: Contains the signature, changes in case of an application change, in terms of configuration or programming data

Symbol.name: Sw_signature1
Symbol.Comment: Contains the signature, changes in case of an application change, in terms of configuration or programming data

Symbol.name: Sw_sl1address
Symbol.Comment: Address of port 1, when bit %S101 is set to 1, you can change the Modbus address

Symbol.name: Sw_sl1conf1
Symbol.Comment: Configuration for use of the ASCII protocol of port 1 when bit %S103 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_sl1conf2
Symbol.Comment: Configuration for use of the ASCII protocol of port 1 when bit %S103 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_sl1conf3
Symbol.Comment: Configuration for use of the ASCII frame size of port 1 when bit %S103 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_sl1postst
Symbol.Comment: Post configuration status of Serial Line 1. The bits are set to 1 when the post configuration was applied for the parameter

Symbol.name: Sw_sl2address
Symbol.Comment: Address of port 2, when bit %S101 is set to 1, you can change the Modbus address

Symbol.name: Sw_sl2conf1
Symbol.Comment: Configuration for use of the ASCII protocol of port 2 when bit %S104 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_sl2conf2
Symbol.Comment: Configuration for use of the ASCII protocol of port 2 when bit %S104 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_sl2conf3
Symbol.Comment: Configuration for use of the ASCII frame size of port 2 when bit %S104 (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_sl2postst
Symbol.Comment: Post configuration status of Serial Line 2. The bits are set to 1 when the post configuration was applied for the parameter

Symbol.name: Sw_state
Symbol.Comment: This word shows the state of the controller (refer F1 help for details)

Symbol.name: Sw_tm1counter
Symbol.Comment: Contains the absolute timer counter (1st word)

Symbol.name: Sw_tm2counter
Symbol.Comment: Contains the absolute timer counter (2° word)

Symbol.name: Sw_watchdog
Symbol.Comment: Contains the maximum value of the watchdog
